trans-unit.source: Retrieves an array that contains the logical positions of the tick marks for a slider

seg-source.mrk: Retrieves an array that contains the logical positions of the tick marks for a slider

target.mrk: Retrieves an array that contains the logical positions of the tick marks for a slider

trans-unit.source: The number of elements in the array is two less than the tick count returned by the _GUICtrlSlider_GetNumTics() function.

seg-source.mrk: The number of elements in the array is two less than the tick count returned by the _GUICtrlSlider_GetNumTics() function.

target.mrk: The number of elements in the array is two less than the tick count returned by the _GUICtrlSlider_GetNumTics() function.

trans-unit.source: Note that the values in the array may include duplicate positions and may not be in sequential order.

seg-source.mrk: Note that the values in the array may include duplicate positions and may not be in sequential order.

target.mrk: Note that the values in the array may include duplicate positions and may not be in sequential order.

trans-unit.source: The data in the returned array is valid until you change the slider's tick marks.

seg-source.mrk: The data in the returned array is valid until you change the slider's tick marks.

target.mrk: The data in the returned array is valid until you change the slider's tick marks.

trans-unit.source: The elements of the array specify the logical positions of the sliders's tick marks, not including the first and last tick marks created by the slider.

seg-source.mrk: The elements of the array specify the logical positions of the sliders's tick marks, not including the first and last tick marks created by the slider.

target.mrk: The elements of the array specify the logical positions of the sliders's tick marks, not including the first and last tick marks created by the slider.

trans-unit.source: The logical positions can be any of the integer values in the sliders's range of minimum to maximum slider positions.

seg-source.mrk: The logical positions can be any of the integer values in the sliders's range of minimum to maximum slider positions.

target.mrk: The logical positions can be any of the integer values in the sliders's range of minimum to maximum slider positions.
